kchmviewer
------------------------------------------
KchmViewer is a chm (MS HTML help file format) viewer, written in C++.
Unlike most existing CHM viewers for Unix, it uses Trolltech Qt widget
library, and does not depend on KDE or Gnome.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-50
  libchm0-0.40-1
  libgcc1-4.3.2-2
  libQtCore4-4.5.2-1
  libQtDBus4-4.5.2-1
  libQtGui4-4.5.2-1
  libQtNetwork4-4.5.2-1
  libQtWebKit4-4.5.2-1
  libstdc++6-4.3.2-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding devel packages)
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.9.7-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.2-2
  gcc4-g++-4.3.2-2
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.kchmviewer.net/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/kchmviewer/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack kchmviewer-4.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./kchmviewer-4.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/kchmviewer-4.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/kchmviewer-4.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /etc/postinstall/kchmviewer.sh
  /usr/bin/kchmviewer.exe
  /usr/share/applications/kchmviewer.desktop
  /usr/share/doc/kchmviewer/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/kchmviewer/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/kchmviewer/FAQ
  /usr/share/doc/kchmviewer/README
  /usr/share/icons/hicolor/128x128/apps/kchmviewer.png
  /usr/share/icons/hicolor/48x48/apps/kchmviewer.png
  /usr/share/icons/hicolor/64x64/apps/kchmviewer.png

------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 4.1-1 -----
Initial release for Cygwin 1.7.
KDE support is disabled, since okular now supports .chm files, and
provides the same kioslave as this would.


Cygwin port maintained by:
http://sourceware.org/cygwinports/
